houseData <- read.csv("train.csv")
relevantColcsv <- read.csv("columnsThatLookRelevant.csv")
houses <- houseData %>%
  select(relevantColcsv$columnsThatLookRelevant)
#https://stackoverflow.com/questions/20364450/find-names-of-columns-which-contain-missing-values
#names(which(sapply(dfname, anyNA)))

houses <- houses %>% 
  mutate(Alley = replace_na(Alley, "None")) %>% 
  mutate(BsmtQual = replace_na(BsmtQual, "None")) %>% 
  mutate(GarageType = replace_na(GarageType, "None")) %>% 
  mutate(MasVnrArea = replace_na(MasVnrArea, 0)) %>% 
  mutate(LotFrontage = replace_na(LotFrontage, 0)) %>% 
  mutate(GarageYrBlt = replace_na(GarageYrBlt, 0))
houselm1 <- lm(SalePrice ~ ., data=houses)

medPriceNbhd <- houses %>% 
  group_by(Neighborhood) %>% 
  summarise(medPrice = median(as.numeric(SalePrice)))

firstQ <- quantile(medPriceNbhd$medPrice, 0.25)
thirdQ <- quantile(medPriceNbhd$medPrice, 0.75)

medPriceNbhd <- medPriceNbhd %>%
  mutate(
    priceRange = case_when(
      medPrice <= firstQ ~ "Poor",
      medPrice >= thirdQ ~ "Rich",
      medPrice > firstQ & medPrice < thirdQ ~ "Middle"
    )
  )

PoorNbhd <- medPriceNbhd %>% 
  filter(priceRange == "Poor") %>% 
  select(Neighborhood)

MidNbhd <- medPriceNbhd %>% 
  filter(priceRange == "Middle") %>% 
  select(Neighborhood)

RichNbhd <- medPriceNbhd %>% 
  filter(priceRange == "Rich") %>% 
  select(Neighborhood)
  
houses <- houses %>%
  mutate(
    NbhdPriceRange = case_when(
      Neighborhood %in% PoorNbhd$Neighborhood ~ "Poor",
      Neighborhood %in% MidNbhd$Neighborhood ~ "Middle",
      Neighborhood %in% RichNbhd$Neighborhood ~ "Rich"
    ))

houses4 <- houses3 %>% 
  #House Style Mutations
  mutate(
    HouseStyleA = ifelse(HouseStyle == "1Story", "1Story", "Other"),
         HouseStyleB = case_when(
           HouseStyle %in% c("1Story","1.5Fin","1.5Unf","SFoyer","SLvl") ~ "1+Story",
           HouseStyle %in% c("2Story","2.5Unf","2.5Fin") ~ "2+Story"
         )
  ) %>% 
  #Lot Shape Mutations
  mutate(
    LotShapeA = case_when(
    LotShape %in% c("Reg","IR1") ~ "PrettyReg",
    LotShape %in% c("IR2","IR3") ~ "Irreg"),
    LotShapeB = ifelse(LotShape == "Reg", "Regular", "Irregular")
  ) %>% 
  #Garage Mutations
  mutate(
    GarageA = ifelse(GarageType == "None", "No", "Yes"),
    GarageB = case_when(
      GarageType == "None" ~ "None",
      GarageType == "CarPort" ~ "CarPort",
      GarageType != "CarPort" & GarageType != "None" ~ "Inside"),
    GarageC = ifelse(GarageType %in% c("CarPort","None"), "Outdoors", "Indoors")
    )

houses4 <- houses4 %>% 
  select(-c(HouseStyle,LotShape,GarageType))

#decided after I ran lm5
houses4 <- houses4 %>% 
  select(-c(MasVnrArea,GarageArea))

housesGroup <- housesF %>% 
  select(-c(GarageC)) %>% 
  mutate(
    OverallAve = ((OverallQual + OverallCond)/2),
    
    BsmtQualNum = case_when(
      BsmtQual == "Ex" ~ 5,
      BsmtQual == "Gd" ~ 4,
      BsmtQual == "TA" ~ 3,
      BsmtQual == "Fa" ~ 2,
      BsmtQual == "Po" ~ 1,
      BsmtQual == "None" ~ 0),
    
    SecondBsmtFin = ifelse(BsmtFinSF2 == 0, 0, 1),
    
    KitchenQualNum = case_when(
      KitchenQual == "Ex" ~ 5,
      KitchenQual == "Gd" ~ 4,
      KitchenQual == "TA" ~ 3,
      KitchenQual == "Fa" ~ 2,
      KitchenQual == "Po" ~ 1),
    
    ScreenPorchBool = ifelse(ScreenPorch == 0, 0, 1),
    
    NbhdPR = case_when(
      NbhdPriceRange == "Poor" ~ -1,
      NbhdPriceRange == "Middle" ~ 0,
      NbhdPriceRange == "Rich" ~ 1),
    
    ExtQualNum = case_when(
      ExterQual == "Ex" ~ 5,
      ExterQual == "Gd" ~ 4,
      ExterQual == "TA" ~ 3,
      ExterQual == "Fa" ~ 2,
      ExterQual == "Po" ~ 1),
    
    NotSingleStory = ifelse(HouseStyleA == "1Story", 0, 1),
    
    LotShapeReg = ifelse(LotShapeB == "Irregular", 0, 1)) %>% 

  mutate(
    FeatureQualAve = ((BsmtQualNum + KitchenQualNum + ExtQualNum)/3)) %>% 
  
  select(c(SalePrice, BsmtFinSF1, WoodDeckSF, OverallQual, OverallCond, OverallAve, NbhdPR, NotSingleStory, LotShapeReg, FeatureQualAve, BsmtFinSF2, SecondBsmtFin, ScreenPorchBool)) 
housesGroup2 <- housesGroup %>% 
  select(-c(BsmtFinSF2, OverallQual, OverallCond))

housesgroup4 <- housesGroup %>% 
  select(c(SalePrice, BsmtFinSF1, WoodDeckSF, NbhdPR, NotSingleStory, LotShapeReg, FeatureQualAve, OverallAve)) %>% 
  mutate(
    BsmtFinSF1_OA = BsmtFinSF1 * OverallAve,
    WoodDeckSF_OA = WoodDeckSF * OverallAve,
    NbhdPR_OA = NbhdPR * OverallAve,
    NotSingleStory_OA = NotSingleStory * OverallAve,
    LotShapeReg_OA = LotShapeReg * OverallAve,
    FeatureQualAve_OA = FeatureQualAve * OverallAve) %>% 
  mutate(
    ScoreSum = BsmtFinSF1_OA + WoodDeckSF_OA + NbhdPR_OA + NotSingleStory_OA + LotShapeReg_OA + FeatureQualAve_OA) %>% 
  select(SalePrice, BsmtFinSF1_OA, WoodDeckSF_OA, NbhdPR_OA, NotSingleStory_OA, LotShapeReg_OA, FeatureQualAve_OA, ScoreSum)

The house score is the sum of the basement square feet thats finished (not including a second finished area if there is one), wooden deck square feet (if there is one), the price range of the neighboorhood (poor = -1, middle = 0, and rich = 1 the groups were determined by finding the median house sale price in each neighborhood and then the poor neighborhoods were the ones whose median price was in the first quartile of all the neighborhood medians, the rich neighborhoods were in the last quartile, and the middle was the middle two quartiles), a boolean variable signifying if a house was more than 1 story, a boolean signifying if the lot the house was on was regular or not, and the mean of several features scores (0-5 basement quality, where zero means no basement, 1-5 kitchen quality, and 1-5 exterior quality), all multiplied by the overall average (the mean of the overall quality and the overall condition, which were both rated on a scale of 1-10)

sorry this is so wordy. i just wanted to get a rough draft of what is going on.
